## Quick start

> **Heads-up — name collision on PyPI.** `ai-core-sdk` on PyPI is SAP's
> AI Core client (a different package). Until this SDK is published
> under a non-conflicting distribution name, install it from source
> rather than via `pip install`. The generated `pyproject.toml`
> intentionally omits the dependency for this reason.

```bash
# 1. Bring up local infra (Postgres + OPA + OTel collector + Jaeger)
docker compose up -d

# 2. Configure environment
cp .env.example .env

# 3. Install: ai-core-sdk from source, then this app
#    Adjust the path to wherever the ai-core-sdk source tree lives.
pip install -e /path/to/ai-core-sdk
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# 4. Run
python -m {{ project_package }}.main
```

## Layout

- `src/{{ project_package }}/` — application code
- `policies/` — Rego policies loaded by the OPA sidecar
- `docker-compose.yaml` — local infra
- `.env.example` — settings template

Traces land in Jaeger at <http://localhost:16686>.
OPA decisions are queryable at <http://localhost:8181>.
